    "First is binary relevance classification.",
    "Second is a 3-class stance classification, where the progressive, conservative, and neutral/unclear outputs are mutually exclusive.",
    "Third is core framing task classification.",
    "Because a tweet may be labeled with none, some, or all three of the diagnostic, prognostic, and motivational strategies, we treat this as a binary, multi-label problem.",
